"{\"uid\": \"spectator.org-vatican-denounces-olympic-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"    On Saturday, eight days after the 2024 Paris Olympic Games' opening ceremony on July 26, the Vatican released astatementcondemning \\\"certain scenes during the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The phrase \\\"certain scenes\\\" referred to the alleged mockery of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican's statement does not specifically call out any part of the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It condemned \\\"allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people\\\" and acknowledged the \\\"offense\\\" that \\\"certain scenes\\\" may have caused both Christians and people of other religions.\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.5476333694361567, \"rank\": 0.7463713135122625, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement advocated for the world to \\\"share common values\\\" at the \\\"prestigious event\\\" where the \\\"world comes together.\\\"\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 695, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican also declared that while freedom of expression \\\"was clearly not called into question here,\\\" it should be \\\"limited by respect for others.\\\"\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Theperformanceduring the opening ceremony consisted of 18performersgathered at a long table with the Seine as a backdrop.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999990184096802, \"rank\": 9.248155781052787e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some performers were in drag and the middle performer wore a halo.\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many people have called the display a mockery of Christianity and pointed out the similarity between the layout of the performers and Leonardo da Vinci's paintingThe Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1085, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9241716203667104, \"rank\": 0.08204508663137756, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.431491602857268e-18, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People across the world includingformer President Donald Trump,French bishops, and theMuslim Council of Eldershave condemned the performance.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999758081530647, \"rank\": 2.4118222922777844e-05, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9874597043072704, \"rank\": 0.012604455018207597, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only one sponsor of the Olympics,Missouri-basedC-Spire, pulled its advertising in response to the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1358, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There has been considerable debate over whetherThomas Jolly, the artistic director of the opening and closing ceremonieswas trying to mock theLast Supperor if the performers were intended to reflect the Feast of Dionysius, also calledDionysia, and pay homage to the Olympics' Greek origins.\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.98126361464075, \"rank\": 0.012482635447515534, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 27, the day after the opening ceremony, an Olympic spokesperson told theNew York Postthat Jolly \\\"tookinspirationfrom Leonardo da Vinci's famous painting to create the setting.\\\"\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1892, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.431491602857268e-18, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement came after the Paris Olympics attempted to deny that it was based on da Vinci's painting through a statement on X. Theaccountis now suspended.\", \"from\": 1952, \"to\": 2108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 29, the spokesperson reached out to thePostagain with an updatedstatement, saying that the performance \\\"depicts a great paean feast in which the gods of Olympus take part.\\\"\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2271, \"end\": 2278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9999950873141352, \"rank\": 4.8534582909761795e-06, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly has also claimed to have takeninspirationfrom Jan van Bijlert'spaintingFeast of the Gods.\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jan van Bijlert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics'apologyissued an apology saying, \\\"If people have taken any offense, we are of course really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2514, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999996634142574, \"rank\": 3.3658592274769547e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You probably saw this Wednesday, and your reaction might well...Read More  I am not going to do so well with the \\\"Q\\\"...Read More  In the long ago of my teenage youth (no, not...Read More  A disturbing pattern has emerged in contemporary Jewish political behavior....Read More  Temple University's medical school sent an email this month to...Read More  As the struggling film industry faces an all-time low in...Read More\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2753, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.9095468995966198, \"rank\": 0.09942871121240622, \"text\": 